are bonded together

00:07:42.870 --> 00:07:44.360
into a molecule.

00:07:44.360 --> 00:07:47.520
And you consider the
vibrations of that.

00:07:47.520 --> 00:07:51.830
You can regard the
solid as a huge molecule

00:07:51.830 --> 00:07:54.560
with lots of atoms
joined together.

00:07:54.560 --> 00:07:56.720
And they have vibrations.

00:07:56.720 --> 00:08:00.830
And if you think about all of
those vibrations giving you

00:08:00.830 --> 00:08:03.550
something that is
similar to this,

00:08:03.550 --> 00:08:06.240
you would conclude that the
heat capacity of a solid

00:08:06.240 --> 00:08:09.690
should also have this
kind of behavior.

00:08:09.690 --> 00:08:12.440
Whereas we noted
that in actuality,

00:08:12.440 --> 00:08:20.820
the heat capacity of a solid
vanishes much more slowly

00:08:20.820 --> 00:08:23.230
at low temperatures.

00:08:23.230 --> 00:08:26.740
And the dependence
at low temperatures

00:08:26.740 --> 00:08:28.560
is proportional to t cubed.

00:08:33.150 --> 00:08:36.590
So at the end of
last lecture, we

00:08:36.590 --> 00:08:42.820
gave an explanation for
this, which I will repeat.

00:08:42.820 --> 00:08:48.000
Again, the picture is that the
solid, like a huge molecule,

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:50.910
has vibrational modes.

00:08:50.910 --> 00:08:53.560
But these vibrational
modes cover a whole range

00:08:53.560 --> 00:08:56.150
of different frequencies.

00:08:56.150 --> 00:09:04.630
And so if you ask, what
are the frequencies omega

00:09:04.630 --> 00:09:20.510
alpha of vibrations of a
solid, the most natural way

00:09:20.510 --> 00:09:23.640
to characterize
them is, in fact,

00:09:23.640 --> 00:09:29.970
in terms of a wave vector k
that indicates a direction

00:09:29.970 --> 00:09:35.270
for the oscillatory wave that
you set up in the material.

00:09:35.270 --> 00:09:47.420
And depending on k, you'll
have different frequencies.

00:09:47.420 --> 00:09:54.150
And I said that, essentially,
the longest wave length

00:09:54.150 --> 00:09:58.180
corresponding to k equals to
0 is taking the whole solid

00:09:58.180 --> 00:09:59.340
and translating it.

00:09:59.340 --> 00:10:03.570
Again, thinking back about the
oxygen molecule, the oxygen

00:10:03.570 --> 00:10:06.000
molecule, you have
two coordinates.

00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:09.560
It's the relative coordinate
that has the vibration.

00:10:09.560 --> 00:10:13.500
And you have a center of mass
coordinate that has no energy.

00:10:13.500 --> 00:10:16.030
If you make a molecule
more and more complicated,

00:10:16.030 --> 00:10:18.480
you will have more modes,
but you will always

00:10:18.480 --> 00:10:22.480
have the 0 mode that
corresponds to the translation.

00:10:22.480 --> 00:10:25.010
And that carries over
all the way to the solid.

00:10:25.010 --> 00:10:28.500
So there is a mode that
corresponds to translations--

00:10:28.500 --> 00:10:31.420
and, in fact, rotations--
that would carry

00:10:31.420 --> 00:10:37.940
no energy, and corresponds,
therefore, to 0 frequency.

00:10:37.940 --> 00:10:42.690
And then if you start to make
long wavelength oscillations,

00:10:42.690 --> 00:10:45.980
the frequency is
going to be small.

00:10:45.980 --> 00:10:49.460
And, indeed, what we know
is that we tap on the solid

00:10:49.460 --> 00:10:51.830
and you create
sound waves, which

00:10:51.830 --> 00:10:56.360
means that the low-frequency
long wavelength

00:10:56.360 --> 00:11:00.050
modes have a dispersion
relation in which omega

00:11:00.050 --> 00:11:02.090
is proportional to k.

00:11:02.090 --> 00:11:06.340
We can write that as
omega is v times k, where

00:11:06.340 --> 00:11:10.600
v is the velocity of
the sound in the solid.

00:11:10.600 --> 00:11:16.230
Now, of course, the shortest
wave length that you can have

00:11:16.230 --> 00:11:20.540
is related to the separation
between the atoms in the solid.

00:11:20.540 --> 00:11:23.190
And so, basically,
there's a limit

00:11:23.190 --> 00:11:27.300
to the range of k's that
you can put in your system.

00:11:27.300 --> 00:11:29.570
And this linear
behavior is going

00:11:29.570 --> 00:11:34.170
to get modified once you get
towards the age of the solid.

00:11:34.170 --> 00:11:39.100
And the reason I
