changing as a function of time

01:21:21.490 --> 01:21:27.440
can be achieved by simply
making it a function of h.

01:21:27.440 --> 01:21:32.940
And, more precisely, h
and conserved quantities

01:21:32.940 --> 01:21:36.100
that have 0 Poisson
bracket with h.

01:21:43.700 --> 01:21:47.330
How can I make the
quantum density matrix

01:21:47.330 --> 01:21:50.810
to be invariant of time?

01:21:50.810 --> 01:21:54.440
All I need to do is to ensure
that the Poisson bracket

01:21:54.440 --> 01:21:58.350
of that density with
the Hamiltonian is 0.

01:21:58.350 --> 01:22:01.300
Not the Poisson
bracket, the commutator.

01:22:01.300 --> 01:22:04.560
Clearly, the commutator
of h with itself is 0.

01:22:04.560 --> 01:22:07.510
Hh minus hh is 0.

01:22:07.510 --> 01:22:12.390
So this I can make
a function of h,

01:22:12.390 --> 01:22:15.270
and any other kind
of quantity also

01:22:15.270 --> 01:22:18.610
that has 0 commutator with h.

01:22:18.610 --> 01:22:22.100
So, essentially, the quantum
version also applies.

01:22:22.100 --> 01:22:26.810
That is, the quantum
version of rho equilibrium,

01:22:26.810 --> 01:22:30.350
I can make it by
constructing something

01:22:30.350 --> 01:22:34.420
that depends on
the Hilbert space

01:22:34.420 --> 01:22:36.460
through the dependence
of the Hamiltonian

01:22:36.460 --> 01:22:41.730
and on the Hilbert space and any
other conserved quantities that

01:22:41.730 --> 01:22:45.436
have 0 commutator also
with the Hamiltonian.

01:22:49.440 --> 01:22:53.130
So now, what we
will do next time

01:22:53.130 --> 01:22:55.900
is we can pick and choose
whatever rho equilibrium

01:22:55.900 --> 01:22:56.680
we had before.

01:22:56.680 --> 01:22:59.560
Canonical e to the minus beta h.

01:22:59.560 --> 01:23:02.930
We make this matrix to
be e to the minus beta h.

01:23:02.930 --> 01:23:06.710
Uniform anything, we
can just carry over

01:23:06.710 --> 01:23:10.160
whatever functional dependence
we had here to here.

01:23:10.160 --> 01:23:13.240
And we are ensure
to have something

01:23:13.240 --> 01:23:16.280
that is quantum
mechanically invariant.

01:23:16.280 --> 01:23:21.120
And we will then interpret
what the various quantities

01:23:21.120 --> 01:23:25.620
calculated through that
density matrix and the formulas

01:23:25.620 --> 01:23:29.060
